<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Porting that doesn't lose customers mid-cutover</h2>
	<p>Number portability is where most carrier migrations actually fail. Our process:</p>
	<ol>
		<li><strong>Eligibility check</strong> against LERG and the losing carrier's portability rules.</li>
		<li><strong>LOA preparation and submission</strong>, with the losing-carrier-side coordination handled by VoiceTel.</li>
		<li><strong>Test window scheduling</strong> — calls to the number reach both the old and new endpoints during the window, so you can prove answer rates before cutover.</li>
		<li><strong>Defined rollback path.</strong> If the port lands and something breaks, we put it back inside business hours.</li>
		<li><strong>E911 record reissued</strong> before the port completes, not after.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

